Tarring and feathering
[涂柏油和粘羽毛]
was a form of public humiliation 
that was used often by angry mobs looking to exact revenge during the colonial period
[这是殖民时期愤怒的暴徒们经常使用的一种公开羞辱形式]
victims would be covered in hot pine tar,
[他们会用热松焦油覆盖受害者]
and then have feathers thrown at them before being paraded around town.
[然后在镇上游行之前向他们扔羽毛]
